---
import CaseStudyMedia from './CaseStudyMedia.astro';
import CaseStudyVideo from './CaseStudyVideo.astro';
import {
  opalisCaseStudyImages,
  opalisDesignMethods,
} from '../../data/opalisCaseStudy';
import { aboutContactIcons } from '../../data/aboutAssets';
import { contactEmail, socialLinks } from '../../data/aboutContent';

const images = opalisCaseStudyImages;
const backToChapterHref = '/?highlight=opalis#chapter-2';
---

<article class="scarlett-case-study opalis-case-study">
  <header class="scarlett-case-study__hero">
    <p class="scarlett-case-study__project-name">Opalis</p>
    <h1 class="scarlett-case-study__hero-title">
      An interactive installation exploring <strong>creative expression</strong>, shared authorship, and collaborative public space.
    </h1>
    <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
      Opalis is an interactive graffiti dome with rotating digital walls. Every minute, the walls shift, allowing visitors to draw, respond to, and build upon one another's work.
    </p>
    <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
      This was a two-month team project involving five designers. My contributions included concept development, prototyping, and user research.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="scarlett-case-study__section" aria-labelledby="opalis-problem">
    <p id="opalis-problem" class="scarlett-case-study__section-label">DEFINE PROBLEM</p>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__unself-design-split opalis-case-study__problem-split">
      <div class="scarlett-case-study__unself-design-split-copy">
        <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">
          What is <strong>The Problem</strong>
        </h2>
        <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
          <strong>How can we reimagine an existing area to attract greater social engagement for users of all ages?</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
          Despite its recent redevelopment and central location, Opalparken at Opaltorget remains underused. Our observations revealed a need for safer, more engaging, and inclusive activities that encourage people to spend time together.
        </p>
      </div>
      <CaseStudyMedia
        class="scarlett-case-study__unself-design-split-media scarlett-case-study__transparent-media"
        src={images.problemImage}
        alt=""
        placeholder="Problem context image"
        fit="contain"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scarlett-case-study__section" aria-labelledby="opalis-design-process">
    <p id="opalis-design-process" class="scarlett-case-study__section-label">DESIGN PROCESS</p>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__stack">
      <div class="scarlett-case-study__text-block">
        <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">User Research</h2>
          <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
            Quantitative data was used to validate and expand our initial observations. Although media coverage became more positive after the park’s redevelopment, visitor frequency remained low. Respondents identified safety concerns and a lack of activities or shops as key barriers.
          </p>
          <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
            Combining this data with on-site observations gave us a more complete understanding of the area and its users.
          </p>
      </div>

      <div class="scarlett-case-study__text-block">
        <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">Design Methods</h2>
        <ul class="scarlett-case-study__rule-list">
          {
            opalisDesignMethods.map((method) => (
              <li class="scarlett-case-study__rule-item">
                <span class="scarlett-case-study__rule-number">{method.number}</span>
                <div class="scarlett-case-study__rule-copy">
                  <p class="scarlett-case-study__rule-title">{method.title}</p>
                  <p class="scarlett-case-study__rule-body">{method.body}</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            ))
          }
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="scarlett-case-study__text-block">
        <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">Design Solution</h2>
        <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
          Opalis reimagines the park as a shared creative space where people of different ages can contribute, respond, and create together.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scarlett-case-study__section" aria-labelledby="opalis-prototyping">
    <p id="opalis-prototyping" class="scarlett-case-study__section-label">PROTOTYPING</p>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__stack">
      <div class="scarlett-case-study__text-block">
        <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">Rapid Development</h2>
        <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
          We began with user scenarios and paper prototypes, supporting a fast and collaborative workflow. Peer feedback highlighted potential improvements related to lighting, misuse prevention, and weather resistance.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="scarlett-case-study__text-block">
        <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">Evaluation With Quantitative Method</h2>
        <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
          We evaluated the prototype with 15 participants using a modified UES-SF. Participants responded positively to the social interaction, but felt the experience lasted too long and lacked a clear sense of closure.
        </p>
        <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
          Based on these findings, we refined the timing structure and introduced options for individual participation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="scarlett-case-study__text-block">
        <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">High-Fidelity Prototype</h2>
        <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
          After validating the core interaction, we created a flexible 2D prototype in Photoshop before moving into 3D.
        </p>
        <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
          Blender GIS and Sketchfab assets helped us model the site accurately, while simulated agents supported analysis of movement and safety. Signage was added to test wayfinding, and a final video render communicated the overall spatial experience.
        </p>
      </div>

      <CaseStudyVideo
        class="opalis-case-study__prototype-video"
        src={images.prototypingVideo}
        placeholder="High-fidelity prototype video"
        aspectRatio="16 / 9"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scarlett-case-study__section" aria-labelledby="opalis-reflection">
    <p id="opalis-reflection" class="scarlett-case-study__section-label">REFLECTION</p>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__stack">
      <div class="scarlett-case-study__text-block">
        <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">Effective Teamwork</h2>
        <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
          Our team established a strong collaborative process from the beginning. Clear roles and an open working atmosphere allowed each member to contribute effectively throughout research, ideation, and prototyping.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="scarlett-case-study__text-block">
        <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">Applying Design Methodology</h2>
        <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
          Using multiple research and ideation methods helped us move from a broad public-space challenge to a focused co-creation concept. The project strengthened my ability to connect research findings with spatial and interactive design decisions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="scarlett-case-study__footer">
    <a class="scarlett-case-study__back" href={backToChapterHref}>← Back to Chapter</a>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__closing">
      <p class="scarlett-case-study__thanks">
        Thank you for exploring my world! If it resonates, I'd love to hear from you.
      </p>
      <div class="scarlett-case-study__credit">
        <span class="scarlett-case-study__name">Hang Wan</span>
        <span class="scarlett-case-study__credit-dot" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
        <span class="scarlett-case-study__role">Design Connector</span>
        <span class="scarlett-case-study__credit-divider" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <div class="scarlett-case-study__credit-links">
          <a
            class="scarlett-case-study__credit-link"
            href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}
            aria-label="Email Hang Wan"
          >
            <img
              class="scarlett-case-study__credit-icon"
              src={aboutContactIcons.gmail}
              alt=""
              width="44"
              height="44"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </a>
          <a
            class="scarlett-case-study__credit-link"
            href={socialLinks.linkedin}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            aria-label="LinkedIn"
          >
            <img
              class="scarlett-case-study__credit-icon"
              src={aboutContactIcons.linkedin}
              alt=""
              width="44"
              height="44"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>
</article>

<script>
  function initCaseStudyMedia() {
    document.querySelectorAll('[data-case-study-img]').forEach((img) => {
      if (!(img instanceof HTMLImageElement) || img.dataset.mediaBound === 'true') return;
      img.dataset.mediaBound = 'true';

      const markMissing = () => {
        const figure = img.closest('[data-case-study-media]');
        if (figure instanceof HTMLElement) figure.classList.add('is-missing');
      };

      img.addEventListener('error', markMissing);
      if (img.complete && img.naturalWidth === 0) markMissing();
    });

    document.querySelectorAll('[data-case-study-video]').forEach((video) => {
      if (!(video instanceof HTMLVideoElement) || video.dataset.mediaBound === 'true') return;
      video.dataset.mediaBound = 'true';

      const markMissing = () => {
        const figure = video.closest('[data-case-study-media]');
        if (figure instanceof HTMLElement) figure.classList.add('is-missing');
      };

      video.addEventListener('error', markMissing);
    });
  }

  initCaseStudyMedia();
  document.addEventListener('astro:page-load', initCaseStudyMedia);
</script>
